] is an analytical chemist's friend. It's used in colour-changing reactions to determine the concentration of a particular chemical in a process called iodometric titration.","span_bond_n2":"Let's go kite flying! [N<2>] makes up 78% of the Earth's atmosphere. When it comes to relationships, this triple-bonded molecule has an unmatched connection. Talk about self-love goals!","span_bond_nabr":"Is it hot in here, or is it just this tub? [NaBr] likes to keep that water nice and clean so that they can have relaxing quality time.","span_bond_nacl":"Opposites attract. [Na+] and [Cl-] ions come together to make all our salty snack dreams come true.","span_bond_naf":"You can flash those pearly whites thanks to [NaF]. This molecule is added to drinking water and toothpaste to keep your teeth healthy.","span_bond_nai":"Iodine deficiencies beware, [NaI] is here to keep your thyroid happy. Along with all the iodine-rich foods, NaI supplements support a healthy metabolism.","span_bond_nf":"Some bonds don't last forever. Under the right conditions, [NF] forms, giving off a characteristic glow, but then quickly separates once the excitement is over.","span_bond_no":"These two come together in a FLASH of lightning! As gases in lightning rapidly heat and cool, [NO] forms. Not great for air quality, but still pretty exciting.","span_bond_o2":"This molecule is necessary for peak performance. Mountain climbers reach the highest elevations with the help of [O<2>] tanks.","span_complete":"You've collected all the available bonds for [%s].","span_diatomic":"Diatomic molecules are made from a bond between two atoms. Sometimes it's a bond between the same element, like [H<2>] (hydrogen gas), and sometimes it's two different elements, like [HCl] (hydrogen chloride).","span_missed_notification":"Oops, you had good chemistry.","span_no_match_notification":"Sorry, not a match","span_profile_ar":"I'm very stable and enjoy my alone time. When I say I'm looking for the one, I really mean it. It takes a lot of electricity for me to feel sparks fly, but even then, I'm here for a good time, not a long time.","span_profile_br":"I contain multitudes! I can be pretty volatile but when I'm alone, I like to go with the flow. I have a passion for photography and I'm also a firefighter. That's pretty cool, right?","span_profile_cl":"Swipe right if you have a passion for cleanliness. I have a very reactive personality, so chances are we'll definitely find something to bond over, but be warned: you can have too much of a good thing (I'm best enjoyed in low doses).","span_profile_f":"Everyone finds me extremely attractive. Speaking of attractive, I'm a fan of a healthy smile. My vibrant energy and assertiveness make me stand out and help me to forge new connections with others.","span_profile_h":"I want to be your number one. I keep things simple but I'm essential for life. In fact, I've been told that I'm the most versatile atom there is. You can find me hanging out with a group of (alkali) metalheads or pretty much anywhere in the universe.","span_profile_i":"I'm sturdy, dependable and grounded. I have a talent for highlighting things that are important, since I see everything in high contrast, and I'm a huge neat freak.","span_profile_n":"Let me be 78% of the wind beneath your wings. If you're looking for a plant co-parent, you're in the right place! You can trust me to stay cool, calm and collected, but don't worry, I'll never give you the cold shoulder.","span_profile_na":"Serial bonder over here. I hate being alone but that's OK, because you can't live without me (nothing can, honestly). I love to exercise and keep those muscles moving. Although I am reactive, I also have an affinity for building meaningful relationships.","span_profile_notification":"Hi, [%s]! Start bonding to find your match.","span_profile_o":"Face it, you need me. I'm the air you breathe. I bring a breath of fresh air to those around me. I have the remarkable ability to adapt and foster growth, ensuring that the environments I'm in flourish.","span_q1":"There are three states of matter at standard temperature and pressure: gas, liquid and solid.","span_q2":"Some elements, like those found in stars, are abundant throughout the universe, while others are very rare and hard to find.","span_q3":"Atomic mass is determined by adding up the masses of an atom's protons, neutrons and electrons.","span_q4":"The imaginary sphere of space that an atom takes up is described by a value called the Van der Waals radius.","span_q5":"Electronegativity is the tendency for an atom to attract shared electrons when forming a chemical bond.","span_swipe":"Swipe right on elements that you think you could bond with and left if you're not interested."}